  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The observation through a chart review of persistent pain on neuro psychological functioning
      and how it applies to the community integration with patients that had suffered traumatic
      brain injury.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This pilot study is designed and conducted over a one year period by the PI, who then solely
      carried out this study from recruitment, to patient testing, to data entry. Pain was assessed
      with the Visual Analog Scale and patients underwent a brief battery of tests that included
      assessment of neuropsychological functions, mood, anxiety and community functions.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
